caption: The last 2 times I've ordered multiple drinks per visit and I'm just so baffled about the fact that this location never has the carryout trays. Here I am with 4 and 5 drinks and when I ask for a tray they say we don't have any. I then asked for a bag. The lady say we don't have any. They never once offer assistance or say I can help you carry your drinks to you car. I should not have to drive while  holding 2 extra hot drinks in my hand not to mention they never have coffee stoppers anymore. Your paying to much for the drinks only to recieve this kind of poor service. This will my last time ever going to Starbucks...

I have shopped at this store 3 times and I will not return. The entire time you're shopping you're being followed, there were 2 other customers in the store as well which made a total of 3 customers.  The 2 employees walking the floor would follow you around trying to hide behind merchandise like they were private investigators. The cashier then comes from behind the register to follow the 3rd customer. My Daughter loves the fact that they are always fully stocked so she always gets what she needs without going to another beauty supply store. I refuse to spend my money and be treated as if I'm a thief, especially since they're quite expensive. If you don't mind being followed or you have patience to deal with rude employees than feel free to patronize this establishment. Oh, items are always placed in the wrong space on the shelves leading you to believe that you're going to pay for example  $7.99.  Once it rings up at the register it may ring up for $11.00, if you question why the difference the owner acts as if you've slapped her face. She gets nasty and will proceed to tell you that her prices are the cheapest prices in the area and you can go some place else. Thank you ma'am. I sure will.
